AGI - Despite the protests of the international community, the Israeli army continues the offensive to Rafah>, a city bordering Egypt in the south of the Palestinian territory, launched on May 7 in order to destroy the last battalions of the Islamic movement. The report of the victims of the last night attacks on dwellings and refugee camps in the Gaza Strip is at least &nbsp;22 dead, according to the local press agency Wafa.
&nbsp;
At least 12 people, including women and children, are perished in the raids on Khan Younis and Rafah, reports Wafa, where two Israeli attacks on the Bureij and Nuseirat refugee camps in central Gaza killed 10 more people. For the moment, the call of international mediators to Israel and Hamas to conclude a ceasefire, after almost eight months of war.
&nbsp;
The United States does not give in their diplomatic pressing >.&nbsp; The US Secretary of State Antony Blinken> invited Israel to accept the proposal for a ceasefire presented by President Joe Biden on Friday. According to a statement by the spokesman of the department Matthew Miller, Blinken spoke yesterday with Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant > of the proposal to reach a total and complete ceasefire in Gaza as part of a hostage agreement that would also allow to increase humanitarian assistance throughout Gaza.
&nbsp;
"The secretary praised Israel's will to conclude an agreement and said that the responsibility of its acceptance falls on Hamas," we read in the note. Blinken also underlined that the proposal would "promote the long-term security interests of Israel" and would open the possibility "for greater integration in the region", while reaffirming the strong commitment of the United States to the security of Israel
&nbsp;
Gallant, he told his office, told the American Secretary of State that Israel is determined "to dismantle Hamas as a government and military authority and "in this regard, he discussed the question of identifying and allowing the emergence of a local government alternative." &nbsp;
<h2> Washington's peace plan
On Friday, President Biden published a proposal for a consensual truce with Israel in which, in three stages, both parties would reach the ceasefire desired by Hamas and the release of the hostages demanded by the executive of Benjamin Netanyahu>. Hamas calls on Israel to "reach an agreement that leads to a ceasefire, a complete retreat from Gaza, (e) to the unlimited entry of aid to give refuge and assist the displaced".
&nbsp;
"Hamas welcomed the proposal for a ceasefire in Gaza and now we wait for Israel's response," said the Egyptian Foreign Minister Sameh Shoukry, on a visit to Madrid.
<h2>Tensions in the Israeli Government
The Washington proposal, however, causes fibrillations within the Israeli government, where the contrasts between the pragmatic wing and the extreme religious right, a member of which, the Finance Minister Bezalel Smotrich>, held a series of meetings with the rabbis associated with his party 'Religious Zionism' regarding his threats to leave the coalition if Tel Aviv accepts the new proposal for the release of the hostages.
&nbsp;
According to the warhead, affiliated to the religious community, Smotrich intends to abandon the government before any ceasefire agreement is approved. On Saturday, after hearing about the plan of the President of the United States, Smotrich said he had spoken with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and announced his farewell to the executive if the new proposal had been accepted.
<h2> 12 pro-Iranian militiamen in Aleppo</h2>
At least 12 pro-Iranian fighters, of Syrian and foreign nationalities, were killed in an Israeli air strike on a station in the city of Hayyan, north of Aleppo, which caused strong explosions in a factory, told the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights.
&nbsp;
Since the beginning of the civil war in Syria in 2011, Israel has launched hundreds of bombings against the forces of the Bashar al-Assad regime and the pro-Iranian groups supporting them. The Syrian Defense Ministry said in a statement that "after midnight... The Israeli enemy launched an air strike from the south-east of Aleppo against some positions near Aleppo" and that "the attack caused numerous martyrs and material damage".
&nbsp;
According to the Observatory, NGO based in the United Kingdom and with a wide network of informants in Syria, rescuers and firefighters went to the site of the attack to shut down fires and treat the wounded. The Observatory added that Hayyan is "controlled by pro-Iranian groups composed of Syrians and foreigners". The Israeli attacks in Syria have intensified since the beginning of the war between Israel and the Hamas Palestinian movement in the Gaza Strip in October.
&nbsp;
